spans.text: all titles thou hast gained — Though still the fairest from heaven's bounty flow
the balmy breeze , Thy tainted winds
who suffer , and who sigh with you
who suffer , and who sigh with you
Behold again , at Fate's imperious call , In one dread instant blooming Lincoln fall !
thy noblest friend , Thy Pelham turn on heaven his streaming eye : Again in Her
to sooth a Father's pain — Let thy calm eye survey the suffering ball
thy calm eye survey the suffering ball
The bread of thousands ravished from their fields
youth and age , th'ignoble and the great , Swept to one grave , in one promiscuous fate
the thought : Thy cares , for Her , are to their period brought
Whom all became , wife , sister , daughter , friend , Unwarped by folly , and by vice unstained , The prise of virtue has , for ever gained
Where sin , and pain , and error are no more
